Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York City:
• In Bedford Stuyvesant, a two-bedroom, two-and-a-half-bath condo with a washer/dryer, on three levels plus a private roof deck in a 2015 three-unit building with a video intercom.
• In Flatiron, a spacious loft with one bathroom, 13-foot ceilings and a private laundry room in the Gorham, a 19th-century co-op conversion.
• In the financial district, a one-bedroom, one-bath condo with high ceilings, lots of light, and for outdoor space, a private deeded nook on the roof of the building.
